<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 3200, 4100, 4200, 4300, 4400, 7300, 7400, 7500, 7600, 8500, 8600
        Models Built After 05/19/2003 - SERVICE CAB - SERVICE CAB - INSTRUMENT CLUSTER: ADDING OR REPLACING GAGES
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="3">
        <title>INSTRUMENT CLUSTER: ADDING OR REPLACING GAGES</title>
        <para>For adding and replacing gauges use
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1602710">Figure 10</hotlnk>,
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1602711">Figure 11</hotlnk>,
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1602712">Figure 12</hotlnk>
            and
            <hotlnk xrefid="t1602701">Table 1</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1602710" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg16/G1602710.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px"/>
            <caption>Figure 10. Back Side of Cluster: Not all Detail Shown</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>J1 LCD Connection</callout1>
                <callout1>J2 Buzzer</callout1>
                <callout1>J3 Main Harness</callout1>
                <callout1>J4 Odometer Reset</callout1>
                <callout1>J5 Klingon SW</callout1>
                <callout1>J6 Oil Pressure Gauge Replacement</callout1>
                <callout1>J7 Water Gauge Replacement</callout1>
                <callout1>J8 Optional Gauge</callout1>
                <callout1>J9 Optional Gauge</callout1>
                <callout1>J12 Optional Gauge</callout1>
                <callout1>J13 Optional Gauge</callout1>
                <callout1>J14 Fuel Gauge Replacement</callout1>
                <callout1>J15 Voltmeter Replacement</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <para>For connecting optional or replacement gauges two different jumpers are used. The shorter 2 in. (50.8 mm)
            jumper is for connections to the J5, J6, J7, J14 and J15 connectors. The longer 5 in. (127.0 mm) jumper is
            for the J5, J12, J13, J8 and J9 connectors.
        </para>
        <table id="t1602701">
            <tgroup cols="3">
                <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.83in"/>
                <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1.83in"/>
                <colspec colname="col3" colwidth="1.83in"/>
                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1" align="center">
                            <para>2" (50.8 mm) Jumper</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Connects</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>J5, J6, J7, J14, J15</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1" align="center">
                            <para>5" (127.0 mm) Jumper</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Connects</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>J5, J12, J13, J8, J9</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
            <caption>NOTE: J4 Odometer re-set is hard wired (soldered). For replacement a connector is used.</caption>
        </table>
        <figure id="f1602711" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg16/G1602711.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="352px"/>
            <caption>Figure 11. Back of Cluster: Not All Detail Shown</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1602712" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg16/G1602712.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="392px"/>
            <caption>Figure 12. Arrows Indicate Perforations: Not All Detail Shown</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove cluster from instrument panel (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1602711">Figure 11</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place on a stable and padded surface.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use utility knife to score along perforations in board (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1602712">Figure 12</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Snap off gauge and remove.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install new gauge using appropriate jumper to connect the gauge to the connector.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
